# The vendored Mermaid bundle is pinned byte-for-byte by the SHA-256 recorded
# in vendor/mermaid/README.md (and asserted by mermaid.test.mjs). On a Windows
# checkout, core.autocrlf=true — the GitHub runners' default — rewrites its
# LF into CRLF and the digest no longer matches anything. Nothing under
# vendor/ is ours to normalize: it travels exactly as published upstream.
packages/core/vendor/** -text
